msDesc.head: John Wyclif, Theological and Philosphical Treatises copied by Jan Hus

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil. foret tempus sua dominacio

collation.p: VisColl collation. Parchment guards at the centre of each quire.
collation.signatures: Quire signatures in Arabic numerals a the end of the first quire and in the beginning of quire 2-9.

p.note: Top left corner, in pencil by a modern hand: A 164; below in ink: G. Stephens Britt. Hdskr. No XIII.

Centre page, in brown ink by a modern hand: a table of contents crossed over in blue crayon, below a later note in Swedish: Se Wyclif Society, 1901 och 1903; bottom of page by: Apographum Johannis Hus de Hussynetz. 1398.; below, in black ink: Jachesius register: nr 13 in 4:o (index ms:orum ab igne servatorum). 1734 års Kat. Philos. in 4:0 nr 9..
Upper half of : 20 lines of unidentifed text in a gothic cursive hand.

binding.p:
Medieval binding. Limp binding in parchment. Spine reinforced with brown leather plate, through which the binding threads are stitched. Two decorated metal buckles attached to the spine. The outer edge of the extends into a flap that partiallt wraps around the left cover. A brown leather strap (possibly of later date) is attached to the flap. , in ink: No 9.; in ink (barely legible, here quoted from Stephens (1847) ): Magistri Johannis hus vnus tractatus de ydeis secundus replicacio vniuersalis eius de veris vniuersalibus. , printed on paper label: XIII. John Wicliffe; below in pencil: autograph Hus
; bottom of spine: fragment of a label.
binding.condition: Parchment warped and buckled. Signs of contemporary(?) repair on the .

origin.p: Bohemia , 1398. The colophon on gives the date and states that the text was written by Jan Hus himself.

provenance.p: The signum No 9. on refers to the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e). The signum XIII on the refers to G. Stephens catalogue of 1847.

acquisition.p: Taken from Prague in as spoils of war.

summary.p:
Stephens ascribes Tractatus de ideis and Replicacio de universalibus to Jan Hus, cf Stephens (1847)
. However Dziewicki (via previous research) argues convincingly that the first text is written by Wyclif, while the other is by an unknown author, cf Dziewicki (1902)
. According to Schieche (1979) there are 24 notes in Czech throughout the manuscript, they are found on:
. The glosses are also transcribed and translated into English in Dziewicki (1902)
.

msItem.title: Tractatus de individuacione temporis et instantis
msItem.incipit: CApitulum primum supponendo tempus esse declarat
msItem.explicit: quod peccat in spiritum sanctum subtrahendo ab eo oracionis suffragia
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit tractatus de indiuiduacione temporis et instantis quem composuit Subtilis vir magister Iohannes Wycleph
msItem.note: The treatise starts with a summary of the contents, the treatise proper starts on with: Intrando de tempore sunt aliqua ex dictis strictis capienda.

msItem.title: Tractatus de ideis
msItem.incipit: INtrando tractando de ydeis primo oportet querere si sint
msItem.explicit: quod omnis creatura et solum creatura habet ydeam propriam in deo
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit tractatus de ydeis ergo laus domino

msItem.title: Tractatus de materia et forma
msItem.incipit: CVm materia et forma sint vniuersalia mundi principalia restat de eis
msItem.explicit: et in vtroque pimorum graduum nullum ens dicit presens uel aliquam essenciam preter deum
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit tractatus de materia et forma Magistri Iohannes Vycleph O wicleff wycleff negednomu ty hlawu zwycless

msItem.title: Replicacio de universalibus
msItem.incipit: Presentem agrediendo replicacionis materiam 3s partes distingo eam
msItem.explicit: quia lycet rex diuiditur in regem viuum et regem mortuum et depcitum et tamen nec rex viuus mortuus nec depictus est rex
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit replicacio de vniversalibus quam si quis bene perspexerit videbit multo meliores raciones pro eisdem quam contra eadem prime enim ducere procedunt alie vero cum o- --lis et cetera

msItem.title: Tractatus de universalibus
msItem.explicit: Pono finem huic superficiali tractatui de vniversalibus ad alios tractatus de rebus prime intencionis ad quarum noticiam sentencia ista apperit agressurus
msItem.note: contain a summary of the treatise. The treatise proper starts on with: capitulum primum IN purgando erores de vniuersalibus et circa vniuersalia sunt 3a introductoria premouenda.
msItem.colophon: Explicit tractatus de veris vniuersalibus Magistri Venerabilis Iohannis Wycleph Sacre theologie veri et magni professoris Anno domini Mo ccco lxxxxviii in die Sancti Ieronimi Slawy per manus Hus de Hussynetz amen tak boh day

note.p: Alphabetical index keyed to the medieval foliation.

watermark.note: Possibly a tower with three notches. Somewhat similar to Piccard III, II, 1-41.

supportDesc.foliation: : medieval foliation in arabic numeral in red ink, 1-134. N.B. Many of the titles in the bibliography refers to the medieval foliation rather than the modern.
supportDesc.condition: Leaves affected by damp stains in many places, e.g. .

handDesc.handNote: Gothic cursive (the scribe is Jan Hus).

p.note: The page is ruled in ink for two columns. The entire left column and 5 lines of the right column are filled with a theological text in a rapid cursive hand. Bottom right corner, in ink: 13., 9.. This leaf is attached to the first quire, but did probably originally not belong to it.

Top of page, in ink in a modern hand: johannis wycleph th. D. tractatus dup. 1us de individuacione temporis. 2us de veris -tatibus universalibus.
.

Marginal and interlinear additions by one or several contemporary hands (perhaps the scribe). Some leaves, e.g. , contain copious additions. The additions seem to consist mainly of corrections and additions of omitted text.
This loose leaf seems to be written by the same hand and with the same type of content as the text on .

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown ink; rubrics in red; capitals touched in red.

decoNote.p: : plain initials over 2-3 lines in red. The opening intitial on and the initial on embellished with flourishing and an acanthus leaf in brown and red ink in the counterspace.
